description.plain:
“16 Lines ” is the sixth track on the posthumous album Come Over When You’re Sober, Pt. 2 from late rapper Lil Peep.

It was previously leaked through the internet on June 14, 2017 onto Lil Peep’s SoundCloud account, before it was later taken down. A music video was then uploaded by Peep’s videographer, Wiggy onto his Twitter after Peep’s untimely death on November 15th, 2017.

songs.lyrics:
[Intro]
Yeah-eah-eah-eah
She's tryna find the words, tryna find this girl
But it's so dark, I was under club lights

[Verse 1]

[Chorus]

Fame bring pain, but the pain make money (pain make money)
Keep it one hunnit, baby girl, what's your number? (Girl, what's your number?)
Girls numb the pain and the drugs get me numb-er (drugs get me numb-er)
Four gold chains, gave two to my brothers (two to my brothers)
Fame bring pain, but the pain make money (pain make money)
Keep it one hunnit, baby girl, what's your number? (Girl, what's your number?)
Girls numb the pain and the drugs get me numb-er (drugs get me numb-er)

[Verse 2]
Four gold chains, gave two to my brothers (two to my brothers)
Four gold chains, gave two to my brothers (two to my brothers)
I need four whips, so I can give 'em to my brothers, yeah (give 'em to my brothers)
I need four cribs, so I can give 'em to my mother, yeah (give 'em to my mother, yeah)
My mom, that's all I got... yeah...

[Chorus]
Four gold chains, gave two to my brothers

[Instrumental Outro]

description.plain:
“4 Gold Chains” is a posthumously-released single from Lil Peep. In typical Peep fashion, he tells of his struggles with relationships, drugs, and both the pain and luxuries that come with his fame.

Peep first announced the song on his Twitter on the morning of November 15, 2017 (one of his final tweets, as he passed away on the same day).

https://twitter.com/Lilpeep/status/930785216091901954

An unofficial leak was first uploaded to YouTube on April 2nd, 2018 under the title “Gold Chains.”

Later, on May 10, producer Clams Casino posted an image of Peep’s tweet on his Instagram, hinting that the song would soon be released. The next day, it was announced on Peep’s Instagram that it would be played for the first time ever on May 13 at the Rolling Loud music festival in Miami, Florida.

songs.title: Absolute in Doubt
songs.lyrics:
[Intro: WICCA PHASE SPRINGS ETERNAL]
Runnin' up that hill, you pushin' me back
Wish that I can make you want it bad
I don't need it though
(I don't need it though)

[Verse 1: WICCA PHASE SPRINGS ETERNAL]
Sometimes you make me wait and make it like a plan
Wish that you could help me understand
Why? Because I don't know (I don't know, I don't know)
Sometimes I feel that weight, I hold that in my chest
Sometimes I hold it back, other times I'm blessed
Other times I want more, you put me in debt
I want you like Zoloft
Wanna be like so inside, wanna be like
For me want you to be more into it than this
For me I want more than you seem to wanna give
I see passion in the way you turn your back
Money and the ice, I put upon your wrist
There's a silhouette inside, a lucid dream
I project myself on you, then back to me
There's a reason that she doesn't call me back
It is the way, it is the way it really seems
There's a vision of an altar now, me and the one
Some passin' on and out
(And out, and out)

[Break: WICCA PHASE SPRINGS ETERNAL & Lil Peep]
It wasn't somethin' that I thought about
But, knew that you were absolute in doubt

[Verse 2: Lil Peep]
It wasn’t somethin' that I thought about
But, knew that you were absolute in doubt
I just really wanna talk to you again
That’s how I know that I'ma haunt you in the end
It wasn’t somethin' ‘til you brought it up
I knew that you were tryna make it out
Without a single scar, clawin' at my heart
I saw you in his car, swear I knew it from the start
Bring me down, it’s not that easy
Lay me down, just please don’t leave me
I remember you were climbin' on top of me
Why you actin' like you fuckin' forgot me?
I’ve been dreamin' about a place out in Hollywood
Tell my mama that I’m movin' to Hollywood

[Outro: Lil Peep]
Bring me down, it’s not that easy
Lay me down, just please don’t leave me
Bring me down, it’s not that easy
Lay me down, just please don’t leave me
It wasn’t somethin' that I thought about
But, knew that you were absolute in doubt
I just really wanna talk to you again
That’s how I know that I'ma haunt you in the end

description.plain:
Absolute in Doubt is the 4th song off of Lil Peep’s crybaby mixtape, which features fellow GBC member WICCA PHASE SPRINGS ETERNAL. The song discusses relationships falling apart, being pushed away and like the title of the song “being in doubt”.

It’s worth noting that this song is extended a bit on the single version on Spotify. The “outro” listed here is the extension not heard on Peep’s official SoundCloud version of this song. It’s just part of his verse repeated.

The producer of this song Foxwedding says that he used no samples in the production of this beat.

https://twitter.com/flexwedding/status/1010716162349338625

songs.title: Angeldust
songs.lyrics:
[Verse]
I'ma take my time when I'm in it
(I'ma take my time when I'm in it)
I'ma make my mind up by tonight
(I'ma make my mind up by tonight)
No, I can't die when I'm singin'
(No, I really can't die when I'm singin')
I could live forever, wait past the mic
(I could live forever, wait past the mic)

[Hook]
These eyes have seen the strangest things
Passin' by, no one noticed my angel wings
Gettin' high 'cause my life don't mean shit to me
Ask me why I might sing you a symphony
These eyes have seen the strangest things
Passin' by, no one noticed my angel wings
Gettin' high 'cause my life don't mean shit to me
Ask me why I might sing you a symphony

[Outro]
"Look at me Damien
It's all for you"

description.plain:
Angeldust is the first song in Lil Peep’s mixtape named Live Forever. The song was produced by the LA-based producer Mysticphonk, using an original sample by him.

Just like most of Live Forever album songs, it shares dark vibes; melodically and lyrically. The lyrics are mainly talking about Peep’s drug-problem, and using drugs as a tool to escape reality.

songs.title: Another Song
songs.lyrics:
[Intro: MTV interview with Kurt Cobain, 1993]
"I mean it been going on and building up for so many years that I was.. ya'know... suicidal, I mean I just didn't wanna live; so I just thought: 'If I'm gonna die, if I'm gonna kill myself, I should take some drugs', ya'know.. huh"

[Verse 1]
I remember when you used to hold me close and say you love me (Say you love me)
Now you actin' like a ghost and that's okay, I know I'm ugly (I know I'm ugly)
Now I'm swervin' in the ghost and I'm okay, I'm gettin' money (I'm gettin' money)
Now I'm switchin' up the coast, get out my way I stop for nothin' (I stop for.. Skrrt)

[Bridge]
Give me some time and give me your patience (Patience)
Came in the game last month, fuck the game, I'm done (I'm done)
Give me a sign and I'm gonna take it (Ahh)
Whatever way I want, bitch, I get paid up front (Clique.. Clique)

[Verse 2]
I'm gettin' mine, so fuck all your placements (Fuck)
Babyface, I'm done, fuck the place I'm from (Place I'm from)
Don't hit my line and say somethin' basic (Skrrt..rrrt)
If it ain't about the money, please don't waste no time (Waste no time)

[Chorus]
Lookin' out the edge, and I'm picturin' the fall 'cause
I don't want to break my legs and have to carry on (hey)
If I carry on I'm gon' need some marijuana
Put it in my bong, then I make another song

[Outro: MTV interview with Kurt Cobain, 1993]
"May as well become a junkie because I felt like a junkie everyday, ya'know? waking up starving, just forcing myself to eat, ya'know, barfing it back up.. I mean he almost died..."

description.plain:
Bavarian Motor Works widely known as BMW, is a German luxury car brand founded in Munich, Germany that produces automobiles as well as motorcycles.

Many BMW car owners refer to the German brand as Beamer and Beemer. Interestingly, Bimmer is the correct term for the cars and the former are used to refer to BMW motorcycles.

Nonetheless, on “Beamer Boy” Peep expresses his fondness of the established automobile brand, speaks on how people are appearing to view him differently now that he has fame and money and makes references to one of BMW’s most recognizable and iconic models, the Z3, which was most famously featured in the 1996 James Bond movie, “GoldenEye.”

description.plain:
“Benz Truck (гелик)” is the lead single from Lil Peep’s debut album, Come Over When You’re Sober, Pt. 1.

Гелик – Ga-lek (Ga as in “gang”, lek as in “lick”) comes from the German word “Geländewagen”, which translates to G Wagon. A “G-Wagon” is a common nickname for the Mercedes Benz G-Class SUV—a.k.a. a “Benz Truck”.

description.plain:
Lil Peep shares the “Live Fast, Die Young” lifestyle that he lives, through his use of drugs and flexing his money.

This lifestyle does not cater to his relationships with other people as well. His past history with his on-again-off-again girlfriend Layla (aka toopoor) is further evidence to the downside to this lifestyle.

Toopoor further explain’s her past experience with Lil Peep in a No Jumper Host Chat, where she goes in depth about dealing with the breakup and the underlying soulmate-bond she still has with him.

The song first appeared on the internet in March of 2017, where Lil Peep performed it at a live show as an unreleased song. https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=vFGWbtMMJtc

The track uses a guitar riff which sounds similar to the one from Final Fantasy X.

R.I.P Lil Peep.

description.plain:
On “Big City Blues” Peep talks about his love for a girl who he just wants to be happy with, although he isn’t. He tells the tale of his music career mostly involving lyrics of sadness and depression, but wanting to have a love for someone.

The song has a Sinatra-esque title, in his memorial service, his mom mentions that he and his friends would have a Frank Sinatra night every week, and his favorite song was “Fly Me To The Moon” and that he was “fucking great at singing it.”

description.plain:
“Broken Smile (My All)” is the first song off Lil Peep’s posthumous album, Come Over When You’re Sober, Pt. 2. The song was produced by the LA-based producer and the main producer of the album, Smokeasac. The song’s Intro was taken from LiL PEEP’s verse on Craig Xen’s track, “UNBREAKABLE” released in November of 2015.

The song’s chorus samples Peep’s part out of PatrickxBlue’s song with him of the same name: “Broken Smile”, released in 2017.

This song sets the theme of loss, sadness, and desire that is present throughout the album. The title suggests the person that he considered his lover has a broken smile, giving the imagery of a face in painful hopelessness which would be what the other person would feel.

This is the first track from Lil Peep’s collaborative EP with frequent collaborator and friend Nedarb Nagrom, California Girls. The combination of Nedarb’s production and the way Peep delivers the lyrics give off a very hypnotic vibe to the track.

This is one of only a few songs where Lil Peep and Craig Xen are working together and the sole feature from the project.

The obvious topic is as the title implies, about Californian girls.

description.plain:
“Come Around” is the last track off of Peep’s 2016 EP Vertigo.

This is a song based on Peep’s dangerous drug addiction and how he struggles to deal with using drugs and resisting his habit. A cut and mixed version from I’m  Going to Do It by Giles Corey plays on the background.

description.plain:
“Cry Alone” was first teased by producer and Peep’s best friend Smokeasac on Instagram. Later it was then teased by the Lil Peep estate on all social media.

https://twitter.com/Lilpeep/status/1052213200379371520

On October 16 2018, it was announced on Lil Peep’s official Instagram that the song will be released along with a video a day later. Since the Hashtag “#COWSY2” was attached to that post, we can surely say that this is one of the songs scheduled to be released on Lil Peep’s scheduled first posthumous and second studio album, Come Over When You’re Sober, Pt. 2 which is abbreviated to COWYS2 on social media. The video was accidentally uploaded but then deleted instantly. Peep’s mother Liza stated on his Instagram this was due to her “excitement to upload it I gave you all a sneak preview last night.”

 COWYS 2 has been announced that it will be released on the 9th of November 2018.

https://twitter.com/Lilpeep/status/1052920589864718336?s=19

description.plain:
“Crybaby” is the first song off Lil Peep’s namesaked album, Crybaby. Peep has performed the song many times in live shows, such as the Rap-Festival  “Rolling Loud”.

Gustav got a tattoo of the word “Crybaby” above his right eyebrow. Others have gotten the tatoo as a tribute to Peep, such as the youtuber “Jack Francis” and the american rapper “Post Malone”, who was a friend of Gustav and got an inspired tattoo with the phrase “Stay Away”.

Gustav spoke about it on an interview with GQ Magazine and said:

I found myself complaining alot, being very ungrateful for the things that I have in my life.. so I got the Crybaby tattoo on my face to remind me that I have been doing really good, and there’s alot of people on earth who would love to be in the position I’m in, so it keeps me really grateful.

description.plain:
Track #2 off of Lil Peep’s mixtape Hellboy.

“Drive-By” explains the reckless life and behavior of Peep as expressed in the chorus of the song.

Furthermore, the chorus also hints at a possible depression, which is a major theme in the Hellboy mixtape.

On his song “OMFG”, Peep also discusses the same topics of suicide and depression, further proving the idea behind the mixtape:

I used to wanna kill myself
Came up, still wanna kill myself

Additionally, this is the only collaboration between Lil Peep and Xavier Wulf.

description.plain:
Driveway is the 11th and last song from Lil Peep’s Crybaby mixtape, released on May 25, 2016.

The track focuses on how Peep contemplates on being done with his current relationship because of how this girl hurts him as well as vowing to never let money change him.

The song features a guitar-centered production by Smokeasac and a sample from the song “I’ve Given Up On You” by Real Friends.

description.plain:
On “Falling 4 Me”, Peep seems to be fighting his inner demons telling himself and the listener how he doesn’t want to keep doing drugs, but he also doesn’t want to live a healthy, drug-free lifestyle either.

The background vocals are a distorted version of Radiohead’s “Climbing Up the Walls”.

songs.lyrics:
[Intro]
(Cowabunga, dude!)

[Chorus]
I love you to the summer and back

She orders and I deliver
I could never leave you alone

Wherever you are is my home, you know I mean it
They say home is where the heart is
You're the reason mine is beatin'

[Verse]
I will always be here for you
And when I'm dyin' I pray to a higher power next to you is where I'm lyin'
Would you fuck me right on the floor?
I'm feelin' naughty, I wish to explore your features secrets hidden in your body
I been feelin' like I don't have a choice
My only option, watchin' me through the window as I whip up this concoction
Don't you ever take your life out of mine
I'll fuckin' kill you, take you out to the bayou in the cabin with the mildew
And I'll leave you there for someone to find
My little angel, in your deepest darkest corners and I'm lovin' every angle
Baby, you got no where to hide, I'm comin' for you
Your parents could never fathom the levels to I adore you
It's like Palestine up inside my mind, a deadly war zone
Quakin' inside my boots as you waken my every hormone
I'll give you everything I've got 'till I'm gone
And that's a promise, unless you didn't want it then for you I'd be dishonest

[Chorus]
I love you to the summer and back
It's not the winter, but you've frozen my heart
And got me warmin' up my liver
I would never put a knife in your back
The love I give her is kinda creepy, but fuck it
She orders and I deliver
I could never leave you alone
My little mama is mad at me at the moment
Know she's such a a prima-donna
Wherever you are is my home, you know I mean it
They say home is where the heart is
You're the reason mine is beatin'

description.plain:
This is the second song from the EP Feelz. It has a positive vibe to the song as this is a sort of tone we have never heard from Lil Peep before. It also has a dark vibe like for example this line below.

Don’t you ever take your life out of mine I’ll fuckin' kill you, take you out to the bayou in the cabin with the mildew. This shows us that Peep wants to make sure his girl doesn’t leave him by threatening her but he really likes her and would not do a thing

“Fingers” is the 11th track on COWYS 2 , it
deals with Lil Peep’s obsession with a girl (presumably Emma Harris) he has a past with. He loves her still, but knows he did wrong. He will do anything he can for them to have the same love they once had. They have to move on to continue their relationship.

description.plain:
“Five Degrees” is the fifth song on Lil Peep’s mixtape named LiL PEEP; PART ONE. The song was produced by Haardtek, who also produced Peep’s “High School” and “Shame On U.”

Like most of PART ONE’s mixtape songs, this one also has dark vibes which fit the lyrics by talking about suicidal thoughts, depression and Peep hiding his emotions.

description.plain:
“Ghost Girl” is the 5th track from one of Lil Peep’s breakout mixtapes, Crybaby. He speaks on the fact that he has not yet found the love of his life.
Any girl he sees could be the love of his life, but he just doesn’t know it yet, hence him being in love with a “ghost girl”.

songs.title: Give U the Moon
songs.lyrics:
[Intro: Sample from "It's a Wonderful Life"]
"What is it you want, Mary?
What do you want?
You, you want the moon?
Just say the word and I’ll throw a lasso around it and pull it down
Hey. That’s a pretty good idea
I’ll give you the moon, Mary"
"I'll take it"

[Verse]
Baby, I could give you the moon
You know he can't do what I do
Yeah, It's true
Girl, I think I'm dyin' real soon
We could die in my room
Me and you
Baby, I could give you the moon
You know he can't do what I do
Yeah, It's true
Girl, I think I'm dyin' real soon
We could die in my room
Me and you
I'ma keep you in mind
While I drive right by
Say goodbye to the nice guy
I'm wastin' my time
Givin' you rhymes
You gotta give me a dime
Before I do that again
And I ain't trippin', I'm high
In the trunk of the Benz
Is where my women reside
Where my women will die
I ain't got no friends
And I don't listen to y'all
I'm equipped for the fall
And the winter and all
When the summer come
I'ma have enough to get the fuck out
I could buy a truck and
Drive that motherfuckin' truck out (skrr)
Tryna buy luck
If you don't die that means you lucked out
I ain't tryna fuck
I see the moon and bug the fuck out

[Outro: Sample from "It's a Wonderful Life"]
"Mary, I know what I’m going to do tomorrow and the next day and the next year and the year after that
I’m shaking the dust of this crummy little town far behind and I’m going to see the world
Italy, Greece, the Parthenon, the Coliseum. Then I’m coming back here and I’ll go to college and see what they know and then I’m going to build things
I’m going to build air fields. I’m going to build skyscrapers a hundred stories high
I’m going to build bridges a mile long. Well, are you going to throw a rock?
Hey, that’s pretty good. What’d you wish, Mary?"

description.plain:
“Gym Class” is a single by Lil Peep released on March 30, 2016. The track was produced by Brobak, a frequent collaborator with Peep. The song touches on high school nostalgia, drug usage, and shaky relationships.

The cover art features Inari Fushimi, the main character of Japanese manga series Inari, Konkon, Koi Iroha.

The song, along with “Star Shopping” and others, had been taken down from YouTube and Soundcloud following Lil Peep’s death due to Brobak sampling an instrumental that had been copyrighted beforehand. However, many fans had saved the songs and started reuploading them to the sites. The songs that were copyrighted (including “Gym Class”) are now available for everyone on these sites, due to the number of re-uploaders.

description.plain:
Lil Peep’s ”Hellboy” is the opening track of his third mixtape which can be considered as the “title track” of the tape. Peep narrates how he is experiencing this kind of a lifestyle he developed over his fast pacing career. He also refers to the struggles he had been through in his past and how he’s missed at home.

Gus did not pick the name by chance—he knew that it came off as intimidating and scary to some. In reality, the title belongs to a hero who had a massive heart, a book only judged by its cover.

Released In September 2016, songs such as “Girls” and “OMFG” began to clock in millions of views and plays on Soundcloud and Youtube, bringing him even more than he could ever expect. This mixtape planted the roots of Lil Peep’s successful career.

Produced by MoneyPosse members Smokeasac & Yung Cortex, they both have worked on various projects with Peep. The song samples the song Too Bright To See, Too Loud to Hear by Underoath.

https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=63EetspU6Is

description.plain:
“High School” is the third song off Lil Peep’s first mixtape LiL PEEP; PART ONE. The song focuses on Peep’s high school adventures taking drugs in his school hallway and focusing on his music while everyone else was busy chasin' bitches. Some more knowledge about Peep’s school days is when in a pitchfork article Peep said that

“I wasn’t there. I would go, sit there for 45 minutes, be like, I cannot take this. My high school was a closed campus, so we weren’t allowed to leave, so I had to hop a 20-foot fence to run away from these fucking fat security guards every fucking day. Literally. They’d be like, “You have in-school suspension tomorrow.” I was like, Cool! I won’t come. School was forced the whole time. Now it’s apparent that it was never very necessary”

description.plain:
“Leanin'” is one of Lil Peep’s songs, that was leaked together with “16 Lines” and “White Girl” on his SoundCloud in June of 2017.

The song features heavy lyrics about depression and drug abuse and mainly talks about Lil Peep surviving a drug overdose. Peep stated in an interview with Fast Food Music that he had been close to dying multiple times due to drug abuse.

description.plain:
In this song, Lil Peep sends an ironic message about the so-called “beauty” in life, by mentioning many negative aspects of our lives and then sarcastically saying that those things are “beautiful”
By the end of the song, Peep gives up on the beauty of life and finally asks the listener, isn’t life horrible?

description.plain:
“Life is Beautiful” is the third single off of Peep’s posthumous album, Come Over When You’re Sober, Pt. 2. The song is a remix of a previous Lil Peep song known as “Life” which was released as one of his first songs and was apart of the Feelz EP.

The song’s lyrical content dives into themes of life, death, and depression. Peep sings regarding the negative aspects of life while also recognizing the beauty of life. Bouncing back and forth between these two ideologies, the song finally settles on its initial depressing theme with Peep imagining a death alone in his room from a drug overdose.

The song’s lyrical content inadvertently was reflected in Peep’s life when he died on November 15, 2017 from an accidental overdose on fentanyl and xanax. The album itself was released just under a year after Peep’s death.

description.plain:
Both the song title and cover art reference  John Fitzgerald Kennedy, who was an American politician that served as the 35th President of the United States until he was assassinated on November 22, 1963.

The cover art features a photograph of John F. Kennedy minutes before his assassination in Dallas, TX.

The song features Peep’s depressed vocals over a sad piano production from NEDARB, a frequent collaborator with Peep.

songs.title: Little Hell
songs.lyrics:
[Intro: Juno & Mac MacGuff: Juno Movie (2007)]
"You're looking a little morose sunny, what's hitting you?"
"Just like losing my faith with humanity.."
"Can you narrow it down for me?"
"I just, wonder, if like.. two people can stay together for good?"
"You mean like couples?"
"Yaknow.. like, people in love.."
"Are you having boys trouble? 'cause I gotta be honest, I don't really much approve of you dating in your condition.. that's kinda messed up.."
"No dad, it's not"
"I mean that's pretty skanky.. isn't that what you girls call it skanky? skeevy?
"Please stop"
"Tore up from the floor up?"
"That's just not what it's about... I just need to know that it's possible that two people can stay happy together forever"
"Well, it's not easy, that's for sure."

[Hook: Lil Peep]
We could run away
Leave this little town
If you had to wait, would you stick around?
We are not the same
If you couldn't tell
It's just another day
In this Little town (Leave this little town)
We could run away
Leave this little town
If you had to wait, would you stick around?
We are not the same
If you couldn't tell
It's just another day
In this Little town
Leave this little town

[Outro]
~Instrumentally~

description.plain:
“Little Hell” is a single by Lil Peep, released January 30, 2016. The song was produced by the american producer, John Mello, who produced all of Peep’s Vertigo EP, released 12 days earlier. The song samples a scene from the american movie, Juno.

The song is most likely be talking about Gustav at the age of 17, back when he left his hometown (Long Beach, NY) and moved to LA. The song lyrics may be Peep’s part of a dialogue between Peep and his childhood-friend plus ex-girlfriend, Emma Harris. After Peep’s death, his mother Liza claimed that the majority of his songs were talking about Emma, and that he never stopped loving her.

Gustav spoke in multiple interviews and songs about hating his hometown, or what he describes as “the shittiest fucking suburbs ever.”

In an interview with the american online-magazine, Pitchfork, he spoke about moving to California and said:

I suffer from depression and some days I wake up and I’m like, Fuck, I wish I didn’t wake up. That was part of why I moved to California, trying to get away from the place that was doing that to me, and the people I was around. I realized it was just myself—it’s a chemical imbalance in my brain.



Emma and Gustav drawing by Sasha Chumachencko.

This is an unreleased song by Peep that has been performed during multiple live shows, especially on his last tour Come Over When You’re Sober. The song is about his drug addiction and his toxic relationship(s). One of them being Bella Thorne who is most famous for her acting.

description.plain:
On “OMFG” Lil Peep tells how he has experienced suicidal thoughts throughout his life, before and after fame. He shows that his career progressed through the song, but he still is haunted by the dark thoughts in the back mind and doesn’t care who knows it anymore.

In an interview with Pitchfork, Peep was asked about the song, and replied,

Yeah, it is serious. I suffer from depression and some days I wake up, and I’m like: ‘Fuck, I wish I didn’t wake up’ … I realized it was just myself — it’s a chemical imbalance in my brain. Some days I’ll be very down and out, but you won’t be able to tell because I don’t express that side of myself on social media. That’s the side of myself that I express through music. That’s my channel for letting all that shit out

description.plain:
“Right Here” is a Single by Lil Peep, featuring the american rapper and producer, “Horse Head”, who is also a friend of Gustav and one of the creators of the LA-based emo-hip-hop collective GothBoiClique which Gustav is apart of.

This song was recorded near the time Gustav have left Skid Row, LA and moved to Echo Park neighborhood.  The main part  of the song (Peep’s part) is talking about a difficult situation of Gustav, where he’s saying to his girlfriend that he’ll always be here for her, although he won’t be physically here. Gus is repeating his meaning because his girlfriend can’t accept that.
At Horse-Head’s part, he’s starting with a ‘convincement’, and trying to get her leaving with him, which doesn’t seem to work due to the sixth line, where she ‘doubts him’.

description.plain:
“Runaway” is the second single to be released from Lil Peep’s 2018 posthumous album, Come Over When You’re Sober, Pt. 2.

Throughout the track Peep talks about doing whatever it takes to escape the pain fake people cause. From his mom to lovers, nobody can stop Peep from doing what it takes to breakaway.

This song was accidentally posted on Peep’s SoundCloud on June 14th, 2017, but was subsequently taken down.

Its release date of November 1st would have been Lil Peep’s 22nd birthday.

The video was directed by Peep’s mother Liza Womack who provided most of the pictures, and Steven Mertens.

description.plain:
“Save That Shit” describes Lil Peep’s relationship problems with a girl. He wants to know if she’s open to living the life that he is, and describes how he can treat her right.

The video for “Save That Shit” was released on December 19, 2017, after Peep’s death. It opens with a dedication from Peep’s mother, Liza Womack: “In loving memory of my son Gus” and features First Access Entertainment Sarah Stennett‘s daughter, along with Peep’s longtime on and off again girlfriend Emma Harris.

description.plain:
On June 1st, 2018, this song was leaked online through YouTube and SoundCloud.

Supposedly this song was made sometime after Castles II, a collaborative project released February 7, 2017, between GBC members Lil Peep and fellow rapper and best friend, Tracy.

On June 14th, 2018, the song was released for streaming through Apple Music, Spotify and Tidal. However, it was deleted hours shortly after its initial release because it was supposedly released unauthorized on these services.

description.plain:
Shame on U is the 11th song in Lil Peep’s mixtape named LiL PEEP; PART ONE. The song was produced by Haardtek who also produced both of Peep’s “High School” and “Five Degrees”.

In this song Peep expresses his suicidal-thoughts after a breakup (which may be talking about his breakup with Emma Harris, Peep’s childhood friend and ex-girlfriend – due to the time this song was recorded)

The sub-title and oft-repeated line, “love now, cry later”, is also likely a reference to Ice Cube’s album and/or song Laugh Now, Cry Later.

description.plain:
On “Star Shopping,” Lil Peep talks about his feelings towards his relationship with a girl that is slowly starting to become impatient with him. He understands why she feels this way and is attempting to let her know how much he cares for her. He informs her that he just needs some time to get everything sorted out.

The song features Peep’s melancholy vocals over a sad, guitar-centered production by Kryptic, a producer that frequently collaborates with Lil Peep and other members of the GOTHBOICLIQUE.

The song was taken down from most streaming services due to a copyright issue with the sample that producer Kryptic used. In a series of tweets that have since been deleted, Peep’s estate claimed that they were working on attaining the rights for an official release of this song on streaming services.

songs.lyrics:
[Verse]
I know that you want me, you know that I want you
The memories haunt me, I know that they haunt you too
But it's alright, you'll be fine
Baby, it's alright, you'll be fine
As long as you're mine, take a look at the time
It gets cold at night, when you're alone outside
But it's fine, I'll be fine
Pay me no mind, girl, pay me no mind

[Pre-Chorus]
Just look at the brightside (just look at the brightside)
Just look at the club lights (rollin' under the club lights)
I gotta look at the brightside (look at the brightside)
I guess she wasn't the one, right, this isn't what love's like, that's for sure

[Chorus]
Help me find a way to pass the time (to pass the time)
Everybody tellin' me life's short, but I wanna die (I wanna die)
Help me find a way to make you mine (make you mine)
Everybody tellin' me not to, but I'm gonna try
Now I'm gettin' high again, tonight

[Verse]
I know that you want me, you know that I want you
The memories haunt me, I know that they haunt you too
But it's alright, you'll be fine

It gets cold at night, when you're alone outside
But it's fine, I'll be fine
Pay me no mind, girl, pay me no mind

[Pre-Chorus]
Just look at the brightside (just look at the brightside)
Just look at the club lights (rollin' under the club lights)
I gotta look at the brightside (look at the brightside)
I guess she wasn't the one, right, this isn't what love's like, that's for sure

[Chorus]
Help me find a way to pass the time (to pass the time)
Everybody tellin' me life's short, but I wanna die (I wanna die)
Help me find a way to make you mine (make you mine)
Everybody tellin' me not to, but I'm gonna try
Now I'm gettin' high again, tonight

[Outro]
Just look at the brightside (just look at the brightside)
Just look at the club lights (rollin' under the club lights)
Just look at the nightlife (just look at the nightlife)
Watchin' the sunrise by my side
We gotta look at the brightside (just look at the brightside)

I gotta look at the brightside (just look at the brightside)
I guess she wasn't the one, right

description.plain:
“The Brightside” is the sixth track off Lil Peep’s debut album Come Over When You’re Sober, Pt. 1, released August 15, 2017.

The instrumental, produced by fellow friend and frequent collaborator Smokeasac, sounds very similar to “Okay, I Believe You, But My Tommy Gun Don’t” by Brand New.

https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=-oorx2EQ0Ag

This song features Lil Peep and Ghostemane which were both apart of the label Schemaposse and was made why they were both still apart of the label

This song highlights the Shchemaposse  while also pulling elements of both Peep’s depressing flow and Ghostemanes fast-paced singing. The song is named “The Pull Off” due to Peep talking about riding off in an expensive car: “I'ma pull off in that Lamborghini Murcielago”

The sample in this track is from the song Cuando by Contra Todos Mis Miedos which was released in 2012, 4 years later The Pull Off was released.

songs.title: The Song They Played (When I Crashed Into the Wall)
songs.lyrics:
[Hook: Lil Peep]
I don't wanna die alone right now, but I admit I do sometimes
These drugs are callin' me, do one more line, don't fall asleep
This is the song they played when I crashed into the wall
This is the girl I told that we could have it all

[Verse 1: Lil Peep]
This is the life I made and I can't go back to fall
Back to fall, back to everyone I ever knew at all
Back to small town blues, and not a clue of what's goin' on
Back to old routines, and wedding rings and livin' at the mall, yeah

[Hook: Lil Peep]
I don't wanna die alone right now, but I admit I do sometimes
These drugs are callin' me, do one more line, don't fall asleep
This is the song they played when I crashed into the wall
This is the girl I told that we could have it all

[Verse 2: Lil Tracy]
Baby, I'm a drug, you're addicted to my love
I thought you were the one, but you were just another one
Call me Hellboy, I got fire in my blunt
Don't call me emo, don't call me punk
I'm a vampire, bitch, I'm countin' money up
I'm with Lil Peep, yeah, we hotter than the sun
You should tell your boyfriend stop tryna be like us
Tatted on my face, baby, I don't give a fuck

[Outro: Lil Peep]
I don't wanna die alone right now, but I admit I do sometimes
These drugs are callin' me, do one more line, don't fall asleep

description.plain:
In “The Song They Played (When I Crashed Into the Wall)” Peep realizes that drugs, girls, and nonstop shows aren’t all it looks out to be in the beginning. “The Song They Played (When I Crashed Into the Wall)” refers to people basically saying “I told you so.” Peep is also looking back on the people he loved and has had to leave behind, and then looking at the people that show him fake love because of his fame and wealth.

The song samples an acoustic demo from “The Fallen Interlude” by Blink-182, played by Blink’s guitarist Tom DeLonge.

https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=GYITPRPfxsw

songs.title: The Way I See Things
songs.lyrics:
[Verse]
I got a feelin' that I'm not gonna be here for next year
So, let's laugh a little before I'm gone
I’ve been dreamin' of this shit for a while now
Got me high now
She don't love me, but she's singin' my songs (Oh, no)
I don't feel much pain
Got a knife in my back, and a bullet in my brain
I’m clinically insane
Walkin' home alone, I see faces in the rain
Where did all the time go?
Spend it gettin' high while I hide from the 5-0
Where did all the lines go?
Now, I'm so high, I be fuckin' with my eyes closed
She don't fuck with me no more, I'm on her mind though
Come and fuck me in the mornin' with the blinds closed
I can show you everything I learned
While you were away from me

[Hook]
Runnin' away from me, but I'm not givin' up on you
It's just the way I be
It's just the way I see things
Take her away from me, but I'm not givin' up on you, no
It's just the way I be
It's just the way I see things

description.plain: On “The Way I See Things”, Peep expresses how he feels his time living on Earth may be cut short. He also mentions a relationship with a girl that seems to have gone into turmoil and how he still wants to be with this girl, with the feeling there might’ve been a chance they could’ve still gotten back together.

songs.title: Tonight
songs.lyrics:
If I had one night, I would spend it with you
I need help real soon, I'ma die in my room
You wanna come fly, too, gettin' high as the moon
I might spread my wings tonight

I’m gon' pack my things tonight
Phone's gon' ring tonight
Hear the angels sing tonight (hear the angels sing tonight)
No matter what you bring tonight
I'm gon' win the fight
Peep gon' make it right
(Peep gon' make it right)

Passing time, gettin' high in the candle light
Gettin' mine, I be flying, you can stand aside
But a heart wanna die, I never live my life
You can see it in my eyes, that I can't decide

I'm fucked up but my heart still beats for you
Broken heart, can't breathe in the waitin' room
Now I'm faced with the test of forgettin' you
Got the whole club packed, try gettin' through

description.plain:
This is not a solo song. “Tonight”  is just Lil Peep’s part from a song called “Apparition Love” with YungJZAIsDead, Nedarb, and J Trauma.

songs.title: Toxic City
songs.lyrics:
[Intro: Lil Peep & Bones]
Alright, lemme go
SESH

[Chorus: Lil Peep]
Life in the background, up and down the mountain
Then it's back to the flat-ground, hold me while I'm drownin'
If tonight was my last night, I would keep on countin'
'Til the reaper got ahold of me then I would take my last flight
Where ever did you go? I've been waitin' for weeks
I don't think I'm gonna make it, but don't take it from me
So it seems every time that I die, I wake up
When it's time to meet my maker, I'll be ready for him

[Verse: Lil Peep & Bones]
Got your glass slippers on, lookin' like you're Cinderella
Girl, what you sippin' on? Room spinnin' like propellers
Boy, what you trippin' on? I will make these pussies jealous
Watch your girl sing along, say she want an acapella
I could give you what you want 'til my body in the mud
King of the fuckin' swamp, name a drug, I got the plug
Shawty say my house is haunted, I say I don't give a fuck
Somethin's watchin' over me, see me smoke a million (SESH)
Drunk kickin', dutch lickin', he said he can't fuck with me
Fuck this and fuck with me, I'ma take your luck with me
Bitch, what the fuck it do?
TeamSESH drippin' on the 1s and the 2s
Fuck your crew and fuck you too
Edge of the swamp, know the truck go through

[Chorus: Lil Peep]
Life in the background, up and down the mountain
Then it's back to the flat-ground, hold me while I'm drownin'
If tonight was my last night, I would keep on countin'
'Til the reaper got ahold of me then I would take my last flight
Where ever did you go? I've been waitin' for weeks
I don't think I'm gonna make it, but don't take it from me
So it seems every time that I die, I wake up
When it's time to meet my maker, I'll be ready for him

songs.lyrics:
Part 1: Poppin' Pills Thinkin' 'Bout U

[Chorus]
Runnin' away from you takes time and pain
And I don't even want to
So, I'm gettin' high all week without you
Poppin' pills, thinkin' about you (thinkin' about you)
Runnin' away from you takes time and pain
And I don't even want to
So, I'm gettin' high all week without you
Poppin' pills, thinkin' about you

[Bridge]
I wish I didn't have a heart to love you
(I wish I didn't have a heart to love you)
I wish I didn't play a part to break you
(I wish I didn't play a part to break you)
I wish I didn't do a lot of the shit I do

I wish I didn't play a part to break you
(I wish I didn't play a part to break you)
I wish I didn't do a lot of the shit I do
(The shit I do)
And I wish you didn't too
Tell me that you hate me
I just wanna hear that

Part 2: Sometimes Life Gets Fucked Up

[Chorus]
Sometimes life gets fucked up (fucked up)
That's why we get fucked up (we get fucked up)
I can still feel your touch
I still do those same drugs
Sometimes life gets fucked up (fucked up)

Every fuckin' kind of abuse

You would give me you (give me you)
Lock me in your room
Don't tell me the truth
Everything you said (everything you said)
Stays inside my head (stays inside my head)
All the shit you said
All the blood I bled

description.plain: In this song, Peep and Tracy describes a fight within a relationship, where Peep ‘walk(s) away as the door slams’. This relationship, evidently, is very toxic and leaves Peep/Tracy questioning if this girl even loves him anymore. Peep has been trying to help this girl, but due to a fight, Peep belives that he’s messed up and now thinks that he’s ‘goin to hell’ due to this. Again, this song can highlight Peep’s self hatrid, as he blames this fight and this possible breakup on himself. Peep doesnt want to leave this relationship however, as he still loves this girl, but is left questioning if she even loves him back.

description.plain:
“We Think Too Much” is the 13th song off Peep’s Hellboy mixtape. The song was produced by frequent collaborator and GBC affiliate, NEDARB NAGROM.

Unlike most of the Hellboy mixtape songs, this one contains a very-chilling melody and vibes. the song is mainly talking about Gustav hiding his depression, because he doesn’t want to get people worried and stressed because of him.

description.plain:
“When I lie” (fan-made name:Needle)  is an unreleased song by Lil Peep, produced by Fish Narc and expected to drop on Peep’s unreleased album named Goth Angel Sinner.

 Although studio versions haven’t been released yet, Gustav has performed this song many times during his Come Over When You’re Sober Tour.

The song talks mainly about Peep being a masochist, and his feelings about his relationship.

This song is in his G.A.S EP, expected to be realesed early-mid 2019. A studio snippet was recently leaked.

songs.title: Yesterday
songs.lyrics:
[Intro]
Charlie Shuffler on the beat

[Chorus]
Change my name, shave my head
Tell my friends that I'm dead
Run away from the pain, yesterday is not today
Yesterday is not today, yesterday is not today
Yesterday is not today
Yesterday is not today is not the same

[Verse]
Today is gonna be the day that I'm gonna come back to you
I know, I did a little blow and I never wrote back to you
My love, I wanna give it all to you
Baby, I just wanna ball with you
I could see the end was comin' near the way I do
About you now

[Chorus]
Change my name, shave my head
Tell my friends that I'm dead
Run away from the pain, yesterday is not today
Yesterday is not today, yesterday is not today
Yesterday is not today
Yesterday is not today is not the same

description.plain: Yesterday is the 3rd song from Lil Peep’s 2016 project Crybaby. The song focuses on running away from the problems of yesterday. The sample comes from Oasis' “Wonderwall”. Many speculate that the lyrics “Change my name, shave my head” are derived  from Cloud Rapper Bones' song “ShaveMyHeadChangeMyName (SeshRadio: Volume 2)”

Lately i've been flexing hard on my ex

Baby girl trying hard just to get fly for me

She would die for me, ride for me

She wanna fuck with me forever when she fucking on me
Come and fuck with me, baby, I ain't fucking for free
Come and fuck with me, baby, come and fuck with a G

Lately i've been flexing hard on my ex
Baby i've been leaning hard in this Tech
I can see the scars on your neck
And i can see the stars in your eyes
Right now you're the only thing on my mind
Got me rolling, sipping, smoking dope just to get me high
Baby i've been trying hard to get by
Baby girl trying hard just to get fly
